                        <div id="managearticle">
                            <h3>Manage Articles</h3>
                            <p>This module was developed to allow Admin to create any Article in the website like: About Us, About Company etc..</p>
                            <p>
                                To view list of articles and choose which to modify
                                <a href="~/userguide/managearticle1.PNG" class="lightbox" target="_blank">
                                    <img src="~/userguide/managearticle1.PNG" width="100%" />
                                </a>
                                <i>Click on the above image to make it larger </i>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                To create new articles, click update to save changes
                                <a href="~/userguide/managearticle2.PNG" class="lightbox" target="_blank">
                                    <img src="~/userguide/managearticle2.PNG" width="100%" />
                                </a>
                                <i>Click on the above image to make it larger </i>
                            </p>
                            <ul class="ul-number user-guide-list">
                                <li><strong>Status:</strong><p>Choose active/inactive to set whether the article can be used in the frontend.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Version Title:</strong><p>Version cannot be edited. It states how many changes the article has gone through.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Created At:</strong><p>Created date cannot be edited. It states the date the article was created at.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Updated At:</strong><p>Updated date cannot be edited. It states the date the article was last updated at.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Parent Article:</strong><p>It can be set to an article to decide which article the child article belongs to.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Title:</strong><p>The displayed title of the article can be changed here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Template:</strong><p>The admin can set the template for any given article.</p></li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Identifier:</strong><p>This is a unique identifier though which the article can be searched by in the url.</p>
                                    <a href="~/userguide/identifier.png" class="lightbox" target="_blank">
                                        <img src="~/userguide/identifier.PNG" width="100%" />
                                    </a>
                                    <i>Click on the above image to make it larger </i>
                                </li>
                                <li><strong>Content:</strong><p>The information to be displayed in the article is set here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Short Description:</strong><p>A brief description or any related information about the article can be set here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Media:</strong><p>This field is used to add media in the database to the article. Refer to manage media section for details on how to add medias to database and inserting them in the article.</p></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div id="managemenu">
                            <h3>Manage Menus</h3>
                            <p>This module was developed to allow Admin to use any Article in the header or footer in the website like: About Us, About Company etc..</p>
                            <p>
                                To view list of articles and choose which to modify
                                <a href="~/userguide/managemenu.PNG" class="lightbox" target="_blank">
                                    <img src="~/userguide/managemenu.PNG" width="100%" />
                                </a>
                                <i>Click on the above image to make it larger </i>
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                To use articles in menu. Select Primary for header and bottom for footer on location
                                <a href="~/userguide/managemenu1.PNG" class="lightbox" target="_blank">
                                    <img src="~/userguide/managemenu1.PNG" width="100%" />
                                </a>

                                <i>Click on the above image to make it larger </i>

                            </p>
                            <ul class="ul-number user-guide-list">
                                <li><strong>Available Links:</strong><p>Click one article, hold and drag it to the right to insert it in the menu. Choose a preset article or use <b>Custom link</b> to add a custom link in the website.</p></li>
                                <li>
                                    <strong>Choose any location:</strong><p>The two options that can be chose are primarty and bottom, which represent header/menu and footer respectively.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <b>For Menu</b>
                                        <a href="~/userguide/managemenuprimary.PNG" class="lightbox" target="_blank">
