                        <div id="generalsetting">
                            <h3>General Settings</h3>
                            <p>
                                This Module was developed to change website informtaion. The backend/frontend website name can be changed at the top.
                            </p>

                            <a href="~/userguide/generalsetting.PNG" class="lightbox" target="_blank">
                                <img src="~/userguide/generalsetting.PNG" width="100%" />
                            </a>
                            <i>Click on the above image to make it larger </i>
                            <ul class="ul-number user-guide-list">
                                <li><strong>Name:</strong><p>The backend website name can be changed here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Frontend Title:</strong><p>The frontend website name can be changed here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Phone:</strong><p>Current Phone Number of Cicero to receive all queries about the site can be changed here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Email:</strong><p>Current email address of Cicero to receive all queries about the site can be changed here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Location:</strong><p>The Main physical location of Cicero to receive all queries about Cicero can be changed here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Role for register User:</strong><p>The initial role to be assigned to users who register through frontend is set here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Url:</strong><p>The Internet location of Cicero to use Cicero Website can be changed here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Facebook Url:</strong><p>The Facebook url for Cicero dealing with all social activites can be changed here.</p></li>
                                <li><strong>Twitter Url:</strong><p>The Twitter url for Cicero dealing with all social activites can be changed here.</p></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

